LAFIA – Students of Isa Mustapha Agwai Polytechnic, Lafia, on Thursday protested over in­crement of N10,000 fees for late registration in the institution. The students accused the management of the polytech­nic of hike in the late registra­tion fees, and closure of regis­tration portal which lead to the protest in the school. The protest lead to the van­dalism of structure including administration block, burning of institution security post, ICT block, Rector’s vehicle and other things in the institution. HOW NIGERIAN MEN CAN NOW NATURALLY STOP PREMATURE EJACULATION, LOW SPERM COUNT AND OTHER MEN'S SEXUAL NEEDS. MADAM ALWAYS WANTS IT BIGGER, STRONGER AND LONG-LASTING!!! Hamisu Haruna Ladan, the President of Nasarawa State Students Union who was part of the protest in an interview with newsmen said the reason why students were protesting was because of the increment in late fees from 5,000 to 10,000, closure of registration portal. In an emergency briefing with journalists, Dr. Justina Kotso, the Rector of the Poly­technic, denied the allegation of any increment of late fees and closure of registration portal. Bandits Attack Federal Forestry College In Kaduna FRSC Reiterates Commitment To Reduce Crashes Dr. Kotso explained that the management were in the meet­ing over issues students were raising over the registration portal when they had about the unrest. She said the school had been closed for a week to en­able the management commit­tee to investigate and ascertain the remote cause of students’ unrest in the school. “Our school portal is still open right now; in the portal I have about 162 students who have registered today when the protest was ongoing,” she said.